This paper is about detecting and characterizing Sybil attacks in the Tor network, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also involves analyzing large amounts of data, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implications of their findings for users of the Tor network, which could be relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
